{
  "stem": "19923.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother and my-- and Regina, she was only 18 months old, stayed behind in Cologne to at least take care of personal matters and sell the-- whatever family furniture we had.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when we arrived, we were immediately after a couple of days sent to a home in northern Belgium by the sea called Ostend, O-S-T-E-N-D.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we stayed there for approximately three months.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That is Joe, Fannie, Martin, and I.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then after three months, Martin and I were shipped to a boys' home in Brussels.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Joe went to a foster home in Brussels and Fanny went also in another home in Brussels.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Later on, after a few months, Joe joined us in the boys' home and-- but Fannie stayed in this home until my mother finally came into Belgium.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, she arrived about six months later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And at the time that she arrived, they had already closed up the borders, and that is Belgium and Holland and the other countries.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They had closed up the borders because they were inundated by Jews leaving Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they just couldn't handle any more Jewish immigrants.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in order for my mother to get in, my cousin's husband, Kirschenstein-- no, I'm sorry, Rembelinsky.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was Rembelinsky.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Should I spell it?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "R-E-M-B-E-L-I-N-S-K-Y, Rembelinsky.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was Herman and Jack.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Herman and Jack were brothers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They survived the war.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was Herman Rembelinsky who told me after the war that he paid $1,500 to a German smuggler to smuggle my mother and my sister into Belgium from Cologne, Germany.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And $1,500 in those days was a lot of money.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he used the words dollars.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyways, I didn't know that they had been in Belgium or were in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had a-- a sort of custom.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
